OL,6,FMr Podmore believes that officers are
OL,7,Fbeing "thrown to the wolves" as a
OL,8,Fresult of understaffing and inadequate
OL,9,Ftraining, adding: "If you are a young
OL,10,Fofficer on the landing, you might be
OL,11,Fresponsible for 50 or 60 prisoners".
OL,13,F"Prison officers in this country are
OL,14,Freceiving as little as six or seven
OL,15,Fweeks training, it used to be 12
OL,16,Fweeks. It's been reduced and that was
OL,17,Fa crazy decision."
OL,19,FIn comparison, in some countries like
OL,20,FArgentina and Norway, officers are
OL,21,Ftrained for two years.
